sky.football.uk.description: Scottish Premiership leaders Hearts venture to Dundee's Dens Park. The visitors squeezed past bottom side Livingston last weekend with a slender 1-0 win thanks to Craig Halkett. (11.01)

sky.football.uk.title: SPFL 25/26: Aberdeen v Rangers
sky.football.uk.description: Aberdeen and Rangers go again in the Scottish Premiership after their midweek clash. Rangers are aiming for five straight wins in their bid to close in on Hearts. (11.01)

sky.football.uk.title: EFL 16/17: N. Forest v Newcastle
sky.football.uk.description: Relive some classic action from the English Football League. Here, Nottingham Forest take on Newcastle United at the City Ground in a game that saw two red cards and two penalties.

sky.football.uk.title: EFL 16/17: Leeds Utd v Aston Villa
sky.football.uk.description: Relive some classic matches in English football. Here, Leeds United face Aston Villa in the Sky Bet Championship, with the sides meeting in the league for the first time since 2004.

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP Final: Adelaide
sky.tennis.uk.description: Number two seed Sebastian Korda of America stands between Felix Auger-Aliassime and a sixth tour-level title for the Canadian, as the two clash in the Adelaide International final. (11.01)

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP Final: Indian Wells
sky.tennis.uk.description: Britain's Jack Draper competes in his maiden ATP Masters 1000 final at Indian Wells as the top-10 bound Brit faces Holger Rune. Draper knocked out Carlos Alcaraz in the last four. (16.03)

sky.tennis.uk.title: WTA Final: Doha
sky.tennis.uk.description: Jelena Ostapenko's near seven-year wait to vie for a WTA 1000 title ends in Doha, as the former Grand Slam champion faces 23-year-old American Amanda Anisimova in an unseeded final. (15.02)

sky.tennis.uk.title: Tennis Highlights

sky.tennis.uk.title: Live: United Cup Tennis Final
sky.tennis.uk.description: Iga Swiatek and Belinda Bencic get the 2026 United Cup final between Poland and Switzerland underway, while Hubert Hurkacz and Stan Wawrinka collide ahead of the mixed doubles.

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP Final: Monte Carlo
sky.tennis.uk.description: Chasing a sixth ATP 1000 title and a first in Monte-Carlo, 21-year-old Spaniard Carlos Alcaraz competes in a blockbuster clash with first-time Masters finalist Lorenzo Musetti. (13.04)

Film4.uk.title: The Adjustment Bureau
Film4.uk.description: (2011) Romance meets sci-fi thriller. Matt Damon and Emily Blunt star as a politician and a dancer who begin to suspect that a shadowy group of men are interfering with their lives.

Film4.uk.title: Pearl
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Ti West's exuberant retro horror and prequel to X. Mia Goth is Pearl - a twisted Dorothy who wants to dance up the yellow brick road to movie stardom. Can a seedy projectionist help?

Film4.uk.title: X
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Ti West's acclaimed grindhouse horror with Mia Goth. Some adult filmmakers inexplicably choose a ramshackle house in the Bible-Belt wilderness to shoot a film. It's gonna get nasty.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: The Art of Racing in the Rain
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Touching comedy-drama. An ageing golden retriever (voiced by Kevin Costner) tells the story of his life with his best pal, a budding Formula 1 driver.

Film4.uk.title: Think Like a Dog
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Cheeky comedy with Megan Fox. A young science prodigy (Gabriel Bateman) invents a piece of tech that lets him and his pet dog communicate with each other telepathically.

Film4.uk.title: Sword of Sherwood Forest
Film4.uk.description: (1960) Adventure with Richard Greene, Peter Cushing and a young Oliver Reed. Can Robin Hood foil the villainous Sheriff of Nottingham's evil plan to murder the Archbishop of Canterbury?

Film4.uk.title: Film4 Interview Programmes:...
Film4.uk.description: ...Talking Film: Stars and directors talk about making movies in this compendium of personal and practical reflections. Features Danny Boyle, Amy Schumer, Chiwetel Ejiofor and more.

Film4.uk.title: Rat Race
Film4.uk.description: (2001) Comedy. A Las Vegas casino-owner sets up a unique game for six punters: a race across America, hunting for $2m. Starring John Cleese, Rowan Atkinson and Whoopi Goldberg.

Film4.uk.title: The Greatest Showman
Film4.uk.description: (2017) Hugh Jackman, Zac Efron and Michelle Williams star in the Golden-Globe-winning, toe-tapping smash hit musical about the life and times of P.T. Barnum, who created the circus.

Film4.uk.title: The Equalizer 2
